A close-up high-contrast computational fluid dynamics (CFD) cross-section visualization tracking airflow acceleration over a semi-rigid carbon fiber flight armor wing profile. Rows of illuminated bright turquoise laser tracer streams and cleanroom smoke particles flow glass-smooth over the upper airfoil camber. At the extreme trailing edges, the flexible deep-purple TPU slots of the eagle-slotted vortextips are shown twisting slightly to successfully break a large drag vortex into miniature low-energy spirals, high speed cross-lighting, photorealistic gas-dynamic textures, 8k --ar 16:9
